      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get the \"balanced\" thing, but that feels like a bit of an easy answer. if you actually look at the numbers, isn't it kind of reckless to keep borrowing money for social programs when the debt is already so high? like, doesn't that just bake in a crisis for the next generation?",
